                <!-- 游戏基础 -->
                <h2 id="basics">🎮 What is Taming.io?</h2>
                
                <figure class="game-screenshot">
                    <img src="../images/games/taming-io/screenshot-1.jpg" alt="Taming.io gameplay showing pet taming" loading="lazy">
                    <figcaption>Tame pets and build your army!</figcaption>
                </figure>

                <h3>Why Play Taming.io?</h3>
                <p>
                    Taming.io combines survival, strategy, and pet collection in a colorful multiplayer world. Here's what makes it special:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>🐾 <strong>Tame & Evolve</strong> - Over 30 pets with unique special abilities</li>
                    <li>🏰 <strong>Base Building</strong> - Construct defenses against invaders</li>
                    <li>⚔️ <strong>PvP Battles</strong> - Fight players from around the world</li>
                    <li>✨ <strong>Elemental Powers</strong> - Fire, ice, lightning, and more</li>
                </ul>

                <!-- Controls -->
                <h2 id="controls">🎮 Controls</h2>
                <figure class="game-screenshot">
                    <img src="../images/games/taming-io/screenshot-2.jpg" alt="Taming.io gameplay interface" loading="lazy">
                    <figcaption>Master the controls</figcaption>
                </figure>

                <h3>Basic Controls</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>WASD / Arrow Keys</strong> - Move your character<br>
                    <strong>Left Click</strong> - Attack / Gather resources<br>
                    <strong>Right Click / Space</strong> - Gather resources / Dash<br>
                    <strong>B</strong> - Open build menu<br>
                    <strong>E</strong> - Pet management<br>
                    <strong>C</strong> - Open shop
                </p>

                <h3>Pet Commands</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>🛡️ Shield Button</strong> - Your pet protects you from attacks<br>
                    <strong>⚔️ Sword Button</strong> - Pet attacks nearby enemies automatically<br>
                    <strong>✋ Hand Button</strong> - Pet stays in current position<br>
                    <strong>✨ Skill Button</strong> - Activate pet's special ability<br>
                    <strong>RMB (Right Mouse Button)</strong> - Move individual pet<br>
                    <strong>SHIFT + 1/2/3</strong> - Cast all spells instantly
                </p>

                <!-- Resources -->
                <h2 id="resources">⛏️ Resources & Gathering</h2>
                <figure class="game-screenshot">
                    <img src="../images/games/taming-io/screenshot-3.jpg" alt="Taming.io resource gathering" loading="lazy">
                    <figcaption>Collect resources strategically</figcaption>
                </figure>

                <h3>The Four Primary Resources</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>🪵 Wood</strong> - Harvest from trees. Essential for basic tools, walls, and early structures.<br><br>
                    <strong>🪨 Stone</strong> - Found near rocks. Needed for stronger weapons and advanced buildings.<br><br>
                    <strong>🍎 Food</strong> - Collect from animals or berries. Maintains health and stamina.<br><br>
                    <strong>🪙 Gold</strong> - The most valuable resource. Used for shop purchases and determines your score.
                </p>

                <div class="tip-box">
                    <div class="tip-title">💡 Age System</div>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        As you gather resources and defeat enemies, your Age bar fills up. Advancing in Age unlocks better weapons, tools, and structures. Focus on high-value resources like chests and fallen tree trunks for faster progression.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Base Building -->
                <h2 id="base">🏰 Base Building</h2>
                <figure class="game-screenshot">
                    <img src="../images/games/taming-io/screenshot-2.jpg" alt="Taming.io base building" loading="lazy">
                    <figcaption>Fortify your base</figcaption>
                </figure>

                <h3>🌬️ Windmill - Your Income Engine</h3>
                <p>
                    The <strong>windmill</strong> is the most important structure in Taming.io. Once unlocked, place it in a protected area as it generates passive gold income. This lets you buy equipment without constant farming, giving you economic advantage over other players.
                </p>

                <h3>🧱 Defensive Structures</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Walls</strong> - Basic perimeter defense. Layer multiple walls for better protection.<br><br>
                    <strong>Spikes</strong> - Damage attackers. Place strategically to slow enemies.<br><br>
                    <strong>Turrets</strong> - Automated defense. Sapphire, Amber, Emerald, or Diamond turrets are most effective.<br><br>
                    <strong>Boost Pads</strong> - Launch yourself or pets. Useful for quick escapes or attacking.
                </p>

                <div class="tip-box warning">
                    <div class="tip-title">⚠️ Defense Tips</div>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        Don't rely on a single wall! Create multiple defensive layers. When being chased, place spikes or boost pads facing away from enemies to halt their momentum.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Pet Taming -->
                <h2 id="taming">🐾 Pet Taming Mechanics</h2>
                <figure class="game-screenshot">
                    <img src="../images/games/taming-io/screenshot-1.jpg" alt="Taming.io pet taming" loading="lazy">
                    <figcaption>Build your pet army</figcaption>
                </figure>

                <h3>🎯 How to Tame Animals</h3>
                <p>
                    Building a strong pet army is essential for survival. Each pet has unique stats, abilities, and elemental types.
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Find a sleeping baby animal in the wild</li>
                    <li>Approach quietly (don't wake it up)</li>
                    <li>Press the paw button to initiate taming</li>
                    <li>Use slingshots or appletors to improve success rate</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="tip-box">
                    <div class="tip-title">📊 Taming Success Tips</div>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        Each animal has a different base taming chance. Using a slingshot or appletor significantly increases your odds. In late game, reaching 78% tame chance combined with a Tamer's Hat practically guarantees success.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h3>⬆️ Leveling Up Pets</h3>
                <p>
                    Pets have 3 possible levels. Defeat enemies to gain XP and level up your pets. Higher level means bigger, stronger, and faster companions. Use the <strong>Tamodex</strong> to view detailed pet stats, spend upgrade points, unlock new pets with Pet Cards, and overbreed level 60 pets for bonus upgrade points.
                </p>

                <!-- Elemental Powers -->
                <h2 id="elements">✨ Elemental Powers</h2>
                <figure class="game-screenshot">
                    <img src="../images/games/taming-io/screenshot-3.jpg" alt="Taming.io elemental pets" loading="lazy">
                    <figcaption>Master elemental combat</figcaption>
                </figure>

                <h3>Type Matchups</h3>
                <p>
                    Each animal has a magical elemental type that affects combat interactions:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>🔥 <strong>Fire</strong> - Strong vs Plant, Weak vs Water</li>
                    <li>💧 <strong>Water</strong> - Strong vs Fire, Weak vs Electric</li>
                    <li>🌿 <strong>Plant</strong> - Strong vs Water, Weak vs Fire</li>
                    <li>⚡ <strong>Electric</strong> - Strong vs Water, Weak vs Plant</li>
                    <li>🪨 <strong>Rock</strong> - Strong vs Fire, Weak vs Plant</li>
                    <li>🐉 <strong>Dragon</strong> - Strong vs many types, few weaknesses</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="tip-box">
                    <div class="tip-title">🏆 Elemental Counter Examples</div>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        Wolf beats Rabbit, but loses to Bear. Consider elemental matchups when assembling your pet team for maximum effectiveness.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Combat -->
                <h2 id="combat">⚔️ Combat Strategies</h2>
                <figure class="game-screenshot">
                    <img src="../images/games/taming-io/screenshot-2.jpg" alt="Taming.io combat gameplay" loading="lazy">
                    <figcaption>Win more battles</figcaption>
                </figure>

                <h3>🗡️ Weapon Progression</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Early Game:</strong> Focus on Wood Spear or basic Sword<br>
                    <strong>Mid Game:</strong> Hunt for Gold Spear, then upgrade to Bow<br>
                    <strong>Late Game:</strong> Sapphire Sword, Daggers, or Hammers for maximum damage
                </p>

                <h3>🎯 PvP Tips</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use environment (trees, mobs) to dodge enemies</li>
                    <li>Place double spikes behind you when running away</li>
                    <li>Keep distance with fast mounts (Owl, Horse, Dragon)</li>
                    <li>Arrow damage is 2.5x against mounted pets - dismount if needed</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>🏴 Base Raiding Strategies</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Team Raid:</strong> Coordinate with friends for overwhelming force</li>
                    <li><strong>Turret Raid:</strong> Place max-level turrets near weak points</li>
                    <li><strong>Snowy Raid:</strong> Use Snow Animals (Wolf, Bear, Rabbit) for massive structure damage</li>
                    <li><strong>Snipe Raid:</strong> Use Fairy, Stingray, or Seahorse abilities that penetrate walls</li>
                </ul>

                <!-- Pro Tips -->
                <h2 id="tips">💎 Pro Tips</h2>
                
                <div class="tip-box">
                    <div class="tip-title">🏆 Pro Tip #1</div>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        <strong>Build Near Resources.</strong> Place your base close to wood and stone deposits. You'll need them constantly for upgrades and defense.
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tip-box">
                    <div class="tip-title">🏆 Pro Tip #2</div>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        <strong>Prioritize Windmill.</strong> Get your windmill operational as soon as possible. Passive income is the key to competitive ranking.
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tip-box">
                    <div class="tip-title">🏆 Pro Tip #3</div>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        <strong>Balance Offense and Defense.</strong> Don't neglect either side. Strong pets need good equipment, and good equipment needs gold.
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tip-box">
                    <div class="tip-title">🏆 Pro Tip #4</div>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        <strong>Join a Team.</strong> Cooperation beats solo play. Team up with friends to build massive shared bases and dominate.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- FAQ -->
                <h2 id="faq">❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What's the best starter pet?</h3>
                    <p>
                        It depends on your strategy. <strong>Wolf</strong> is great for offense, <strong>Bear</strong> provides durability, and <strong>Rabbit</strong> offers speed for early resource gathering.
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Can I play with friends?</h3>
                    <p>
                        Yes! Share your server link with friends to form a clan. You can build shared bases and coordinate attacks together.
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How do I get rare pets?</h3>
                    <p>
                        Defeat boss animals for Pet Cards. Collect 50 cards to unlock a pet, 100 for 2 pets, and 150 for 3 pets at spawn.
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Is Taming.io free?</h3>
                    <p>
                        Yes! It's 100% free to play at <a href="https://tamingio.org" target="_blank">tamingio.org</a>. Create an account to save your progress.
                    </p>
                </div>

